title: La battaglia di Algeri
overview: In the 1950s, fear and violence escalate as the people of Algiers fight for independence from the French government.

title: Kis Uykusu
overview: A hotel owner and landlord in a remote Turkish village deals with conflicts within his family and a tenant behind on his rent.

title: Todo sobre mi madre
overview: Young Esteban wants to become a writer and also to discover the identity of his second mother, a trans woman, carefully concealed by his mother Manuela.

title: Forrest Gump
overview: The presidencies of Kennedy and Johnson, the events of Vietnam, Watergate and other historical events unfold through the perspective of an Alabama man with an IQ of 75, whose only desire is to be reunited with his childhood sweetheart.

title: Le notti di Cabiria
overview: A waifish prostitute wanders the streets of Rome looking for true love but finds only heartbreak.

title: La piel que habito
overview: A brilliant plastic surgeon, haunted by past tragedies, creates a type of synthetic skin that withstands any kind of damage. His guinea pig: a mysterious and volatile woman who holds the key to his obsession.

title: Sling Blade
overview: Karl Childers, a simple man hospitalized since his childhood murder of his mother and her lover, is released to start a new life in a small town.

title: Jules et Jim
overview: Decades of a love triangle concerning two friends and an impulsive woman.

title: Portrait de la jeune fille en feu
overview: On an isolated island in Brittany at the end of the eighteenth century, a female painter is obliged to paint a wedding portrait of a young woman.

title: Vivre sa vie: Film en douze tableaux
overview: Twelve episodic tales in the life of a Parisian woman and her slow descent into prostitution.

title: La Strada
overview: A care-free girl is sold to a traveling entertainer, consequently enduring physical and emotional pain along the way.

title: The Florida Project
overview: Set over one summer, the film follows precocious six-year-old Moonee as she courts mischief and adventure with her ragtag playmates and bonds with her rebellious but caring mother, all while living in the shadows of Walt Disney World.

title: Jodaeiye Nader az Simin
overview: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

title: Doctor Zhivago
overview: The life of a Russian physician and poet who, although married to another, falls in love with a political activist's wife and experiences hardship during World War I and then the October Revolution.

title: Le passé
overview: An Iranian man deserts his French wife and her two children to return to his homeland. Meanwhile, his wife starts up a new relationship, a reality her husband confronts upon his wife's request for a divorce.

title: The Shawshank Redemption
overview: Two imprisoned men bond over a number of years, finding solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.

title: Fanny och Alexander
overview: Two young Swedish children experience the many comedies and tragedies of their family, the Ekdahls.

title: Rain Man
overview: Selfish yuppie Charlie Babbitt's father left a fortune to his savant brother Raymond and a pittance to Charlie; they travel cross-country.

title: Django Unchained
overview: With the help of a German bounty hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal Mississippi plantation owner.

title: Soorarai Pottru
overview: Nedumaaran Rajangam "Maara" sets out to make the common man fly and in the process takes on the world's most capital intensive industry and several enemies who stand in his way.
